<br>
You want to know the down side of a monk?  Let's see.  <br>
<br>
#1  I've destroy more platinums soloing cause I couldn't carry it than most people have seen in their entire eq career.<br>
<br>
#2  Being just as good a tank as a warrior if not better, supposed to be just as good a tank as a warrior and getting nerfed because others don't know the nature of combat.<br>
<br>
#3 Not having a taunt button.<br>
<br>
#4 Not having a 3 min def disc or the HPs of a warrior that allows them to be the center of the attention on a raid.  Instead having an 8 second def disc that does little more than allow you to pass aggro to the warrior.<br>
<br>
#5 Not having the weapons with the cool effects.  <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Monks and warriors are one in the same.  They just have different roles.  There is no reason a monk shouldn't be as good or better tank in atleast some situations.  <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Everyone can list a down side of their class.  Hell I think, what is the down side of being a MB wizard?  Oh then hmm, I think about the impending nerf on wizards MB.  <br>
<br>
<br>
Wizards are supposed to be able to get together and 12 of them take out Sont or something like that.  That's what wizards live to do and live to be.  <br>
<br>
You can't take things away simply because you don't know how to deal with it without rewriting a ton of code to save money that isn't being spent on customer service.  Lol that's for sure.<br>
